															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225844" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1519192086 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Feb 2018 05:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3717231">
									

<p>It's not really that I care about the format exactly. I don't, for example, care that the CICAPOCO block is absent. It is more that the section headers should relate to the contents. In an SCP article, you expect the SCPs section to be about <em>procedures</em> for <em>containment</em> that are <em>special</em>. In an SPC, you similarly expect the SCPs section to be about <em>capabilities</em> for <em>pummeling</em> <em>selachian entities</em>.</p>
<p>This is like one of those articles that inexplicably puts the description in the SCPs and the SCPs in the Description. Which notably would also typically result in a downvote from me.</p>
<p>Although it is also pretty clear that I am the only one who cares&#8230;</p>

							</div>

								
